  "datePublished": "2026-03-08",
  "description": "Llama is a family of open-weight large language models from Meta. The Llama architecture is effectively the reference implementation for the open-weight LLM ecosystem — llama.cpp is named after it, and most other model families are compatible with tools built for Llama.\nGenerations: Llama 1 (2023, 7B–65B), Llama 2 (mid-2023, 7B–70B), Llama 3 (2024, 8B/70B), Llama 3.1 (mid-2024, 8B/70B/405B with 128K context), Llama 3.2 (late 2024, 1B/3B text-only plus 11B/90B multimodal), Llama 4 (April 2025, mixture-of-experts).\n",
  "name": "Llama",
